Why does a network tool need location permission!!!!?
replyContent: Because wifi network names (SSIDs) and MACs (BSSIDs) are unique to routers around you and can be used to find where you are (check for instance https://wigle.net). If these values weren't protected by the permission, apps could get your location without you knowing it.
